# Edward Wickham (priest)

Edward Charles Wickham (1834â€“1910) was an English Anglican priest, Dean of Lincoln from 1894 to 1910.
Born on 7 December 1834, he was educated at Winchester and New College, Oxford, being appointed a Probationary Scholar at 17 and eventually rose to be a Fellow. He was Headmaster of Wellington College from 1873 to 1893 before his appointment to the Deanery. He died on 18 August 1910.
